{"title_page": "1990 Brit Awards", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=October 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Infobox award\n|name = 10th Brit Awards\n|image = \n|date = 18 February 1990\n|venue = [[Dominion Theatre]]\n|host = [[Cathy McGowan (presenter)|Cathy McGowan]]\n| network = [[BBC]]\n|previous = [[1989 Brit Awards|1989]]\n|main = [[Brit Awards]]\n|next = [[1991 Brit Awards|1991]]\n|most_awards = [[Fine Young Cannibals]], [[Neneh Cherry]] and [[Phil Collins]] (2)\n|most_nominations = [[Lisa Stansfield]] and [[Soul II Soul]] (4)\n}}\nThe '''1990 [[Brit Awards]]''' were the 10th edition of the biggest annual [[pop music]] awards in the [[United Kingdom]]. They are run by the [[British Phonographic Industry]] and took place on 18 February 1990. The ceremony was held at the [[Dominion Theatre]] in [[London]] for the first time, having previously been held at the [[Royal Albert Hall]], and was hosted by [[Cathy McGowan (presenter)|Cathy McGowan]].\n\n==Performances==\n*[[Lisa Stansfield]] \u2013 \"[[All Around the World (Lisa Stansfield song)|All Around the World]]\"\n*[[Neneh Cherry]] \u2013 \"[[Manchild (song)|Manchild]]\"\n*[[Nigel Kennedy]] \u2013 Vivaldi's Four Seasons\n*Various Artists with appearance by [[The Cookie Crew]] \u2013 \"The Brits 1990 (Dance Medley)\"\n*[[Phil Collins]] \u2013 \"[[Another Day in Paradise]]\"\n*[[Soul II Soul]] \u2013 What Is Soul II Soul\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#bebebe\"\n! width=\"50%\"|[[Brit Award for British Album of the Year|British Album of the Year]]<br/><small>(presented by [[Liza Minnelli]])</small>\n! width=\"50%\"|[[Brit Award for British Producer of the Year|British Producer of the Year]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*'''[[Fine Young Cannibals]]''' \u2013 '''''[[The Raw & the Cooked (album)|The Raw & the Cooked]]'''''\n**[[Eurythmics]] \u2013 ''[[We Too Are One]]''\n**[[Simply Red]] \u2013 ''[[A New Flame]]''\n**[[Soul II Soul]] \u2013 ''[[Club Classics Vol. One]]''\n**[[Tears for Fears]] \u2013 ''[[The Seeds of Love]]''\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*'''[[David A. Stewart|Dave Stewart]]'''\n**[[Coldcut]]\n**[[Kate Bush]]\n**[[Peter Gabriel]]\n**[[Steve Lillywhite]]\n**[[Stock, Aitken & Waterman]]\n|-\n! width=\"50%\"|[[Brit Award for British Single of the Year|British Single of the Year]]<br/><small>(presented by [[Simon Mayo]])</small>\n! width=\"50%\"|[[Brit Award for British Video of the Year|British Video of the Year]]<br/><small>(presented by [[Bobby Brown]])</small>\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*'''[[Phil Collins]] \u2013 \"[[Another Day in Paradise]]\"'''\n**[[Band Aid II]] \u2013 \"[[Do They Know Its Christmas?]]\"\n**[[The Christians (band)|The Christians]], [[Holly Johnson]], [[Paul McCartney]], [[Gerry Marsden]] and [[Stock Aitken Waterman]] \u2013 \"[[Ferry Cross the Mersey]]\"\n**[[Jason Donovan]] \u2013 \"[[Sealed with a Kiss]]\"\n**Jason Donovan \u2013 \"[[Too Many Broken Hearts]]\"\n**[[Jive Bunny and the Mastermixers]] \u2013 \"[[Swing the Mood]]\"\n**Jive Bunny and the Mastermixers \u2013 \"[[That's What I Like (Jive Bunny and the Mastermixers song)|That's What I Like]]\"\n**Jive Bunny and the Mastermixers \u2013 \"[[Let's Party (song)|Let's Party]]\"\n**[[Lisa Stansfield]] \u2013 \"[[All Around the World (Lisa Stansfield song)|All Around the World]]\"\n**[[Marc Almond]] & [[Gene Pitney]] \u2013<br>\"[[Something's Gotten Hold Of My Heart]]\"\n**[[Simple Minds]] \u2013 \"[[Belfast Child]]\"\n**[[Sonia (singer)|Sonia]] \u2013 \"[[You'll Never Stop Me Loving You]]\"\n**[[Soul II Soul]] \u2013 \"[[Back to Life (However Do You Want Me)|Back to Life]]\"\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''[[The Cure]]''' \u2013 '''\"[[Lullaby (The Cure song)|Lullaby]]\"'''\n**[[The Alarm]] \u2013 \"A New South Wales\"\n**[[The Beautiful South]] \u2013 \"[[Song for Whoever]]\"\n**[[Billy Joel]] \u2013 \"[[We Didn't Start the Fire]]\" <small>(United States)</small>\n**[[De La Soul]] \u2013 \"[[Eye Know]]\" <small>(United States)<